scripts.comment: Uses a deep learning model named coco-ssd to detect objects in an image. By default it reports at most 20 objects and only those which it has a confidence score of at least 50%. For each detected object it reports its label (see the variable 'all class labels') and the smallest rectangle that surrounds the object.

custom-block.s: Open this in a new tab

scripts.comment: Repeatedly use the camera to generate costumes for object detection. This requests the faster but less accurate version report at most 10 objects so long as their confidence score is at least 0.25. The defaults, if not provided, are slower and more accurate, at most 20 objects reported, and 0.5 confidence minimum.
